## âš™ï¸ Setup & Run

### 1ï¸âƒ£ Clone the repository
```bash
git clone https://github.com/yourusername/fintrack-backend.git
cd fintrack-backend


2ï¸âƒ£ Configure database

Edit src/main/resources/application.properties depending on your environment.

Local PostgreSQL;
spring.datasource.url=jdbc:postgresql://localhost:5432/fintrack_db
spring.datasource.username=postgres
spring.datasource.password=
spring.jpa.hibernate.ddl-auto=update
server.port=8080


Cloud (Supabase / remote PostgreSQL)

spring.datasource.url=jdbc:postgresql://<your-supabase-host>:5432/postgres
spring.datasource.username=<your-db-username>
spring.datasource.password=<your-db-password>
spring.jpa.hibernate.ddl-auto=update
server.port=8080


3ï¸âƒ£ Build and run
mvn clean install
mvn spring-boot:run


ğŸ—‚ API Endpoints
ğŸ” Authentication

POST /api/auth/login â€“ Login and get JWT
Body example:

{
  "username": "jslim",
  "password": "yourpassword"
}


POST /api/auth/register â€“ Register a new user

GET /api/users/me â€“ Get current authenticated user info

ğŸ¢ Departments

GET /api/departments â€“ List all departments

POST /api/departments â€“ Create a department

PUT /api/departments/{id} â€“ Update a department

DELETE /api/departments/{id} â€“ Delete a department

ğŸ’¸ Expenses

GET /api/expenses â€“ List all expenses

POST /api/expenses/submit â€“ Submit a new expense
Body example:

{
  "title": "Client Lunch",
  "description": "Lunch with client",
  "amount": 85.50,
  "category": "TRAVEL",
  "departmentId": 4
}


PUT /api/expenses/{id} â€“ Update an expense (only PENDING)

DELETE /api/expenses/{id} â€“ Delete an expense

PATCH /api/expenses/{id}/approve â€“ Approve an expense (ADMIN/Manager)

PATCH /api/expenses/{id}/deny/{reviewerId} â€“ Deny an expense

ğŸ“ Notes

JWT token is required for /api/** endpoints except authentication routes.

User roles determine permissions (ADMIN, MANAGER, etc.).

Expenses can only be updated when PENDING.

Departments can be deleted without deleting users

